    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-14T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-14T11:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/830a suppl.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-14T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1918, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1365. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1187. Supplementing Department’s 925, August 22, 8 p.m., our 1069.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d303fn2">Not printed.</note> Please repeat the following to
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DAV1">Dye</persName>: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Department’s 436, August 24, 5 p.m., our 52. <persName
                                corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> has sent us
                            corrected text of cork-makers’ agreement. It does not differ materially
                            from the former text submitted to us by <persName
                                corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> in his
                            despatch of June 7.<note n="1" xml:id="d303fn1">See footnote 1, <hi
                                    rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1188">p.
                                1188</ref>.</note> In consequence, you are authorized to sign this
                            agreement.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
